data.name: The Weeknd And Anitta Release 'Sao Paulo' Just In Time For Halloween
data.description: The latest track "São Paulo" by *The Weeknd* and *Anitta* brings a wild mix of Brazilian funk and dark, hypnotic vibes, just in time for Halloween. Picture The Weeknd’s moody, intense lyrics layered over Anitta’s bold, playful energy, creating a blend that’s haunting and addictive all at once. In the video, Anitta walks through New York with a surreal twist—a singing baby bump that adds a whole other level of eerie to The Weeknd’s verses. Together, they bring a sound that’s seductive, a bit twisted, and perfect for late October. This collab hints at even more surprises to come from The Weeknd’s upcoming album "Hurry Up Tomorrow," marking the track as more than just a song—it’s an experience. Learn more about your ad choices. data.name: Learning to love: Coldplay
data.description: Coldplay is one of the biggest musical acts in the world, ranking #6 on Spotify and boasting one of the highest-grossing tours of all time. Yet, despite their global success, they've often been a critical punching bag. The New York Times once branded them “the most insufferable band of the decade.” The Independent described them as “pompous, mawkish, and unbearably smug.” But Coldplay has never claimed to be the hardest rock band—they’ve instead built a legacy on their softer sound and uplifting message. With the release of their 10th studio album, Moon Music, we dive deep into their catalog and ask the question: can we learn to love Coldplay? Learn more about your ad choices.
